# Performance Rules

## Core Web Vitals Targets
| Metric | Target |
|--------|--------|
| LCP | < 2.5s |
| INP | < 200ms |
| CLS | < 0.1 |
| FCP | < 1.5s |
| TBT | < 200ms |

## Bundle Budgets
| Page Type | JS Budget (gzipped) | CSS Budget |
|-----------|---------------------|------------|
| Landing | < 150kb | < 30kb |
| App | < 300kb | < 50kb |
| Microsite | < 80kb | < 15kb |

## Loading Strategy
1. Inline critical above-the-fold CSS where justified
2. Preload hero image and primary font only
3. Defer non-critical CSS or JS
4. Dynamically import heavy libraries:
```typescript
const gsapModule = await import('gsap')
const { ScrollTrigger } = await import('gsap/ScrollTrigger')
```

## Image Optimization
- Always provide explicit `width` and `height`
- Use `loading="eager"` + `fetchpriority="high"` for hero only
- Use `loading="lazy"` for below-the-fold images
- Prefer AVIF or WebP with fallbacks
- Never ship source images far beyond rendered size

## Font Loading
- Max 2 font families unless clearly justified
- Use `font-display: swap`
- Subset where possible
- Preload only truly critical weight/style

## Animation Performance
- Animate ONLY compositor-friendly properties:
  - ✅ `transform`, `opacity`, `clip-path`
  - ✅ `filter` (sparingly)
- Avoid animating layout-bound properties:
  - ❌ `width`, `height`, `top`, `left`, `margin`, `padding`
- Use `will-change` narrowly and remove when done
- Prefer CSS for simple transitions
- Use `requestAnimationFrame` or established libraries for JS motion
- Avoid scroll handler churn — use IntersectionObserver

## React 19 Performance
- React Compiler handles memoization automatically
- Still split large components for better tree-shaking
- Use `React.lazy()` + `Suspense` for route-based code splitting
- Keep component props stable (avoid inline objects/functions when possible)

## Backend Performance
- Use connection pooling for databases
- Cache expensive computations (Redis)
- Use async/await for I/O-bound operations
- Implement pagination for large datasets
- Set appropriate timeouts on external API calls

## Performance Checklist
- [ ] All images have explicit dimensions
- [ ] No render-blocking resources
- [ ] No layout shifts from dynamic content
- [ ] Motion stays on compositor-friendly properties
- [ ] Third-party scripts load async/defer
- [ ] Bundle sizes within budget
- [ ] API responses paginated where applicable
